. Inversion Method

Finding minimum subarray can be done using Kadane on inverted array. we know total=min+max therefore min=total-max

Steps:

Find normal max subarray (Kadane)

Compute total sum

Invert the array

Run Kadane again

Add total sum

Example:

arr = [8, -1, 3, 4]
Step 1 — Normal max
Kadane = 14
Step 2 — Total sum
8 + (-1) + 3 + 4 = 14
Step 3 — Invert array
[-8, 1, -3, -4]
Step 4 — Kadane on inverted array
Max sum = 1
Step 5 — Circular sum
Circular = totalSum + invertedKadane
         = 14 + 1
         = 15
Final Answer
max(normalKadane , circular)
= max(14 , 15)
= 15
5. Edge Case (Very Important)

If all numbers are negative

Example:

[-3, -2, -5]

Then circular formula gives wrong result.

So we return:  NORMAL KADANE

code:

(helper)  :
int kadane(vector<int>& arr) {
    int maxSum = arr[0];
    int currSum = arr[0];

    for(int i = 1; i < arr.size(); i++) {
        currSum = max(arr[i], currSum + arr[i]);
        maxSum = max(maxSum, currSum);
    }

    return maxSum;
}

int maxCircularSubarraySum(vector<int>& arr) {
    int normalMax = kadane(arr);

    // if all numbers are negative  @edge case
    if(normalMax < 0)
        return normalMax;

    int totalSum = 0;

    for(int i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++) {
        totalSum += arr[i];
        arr[i] = -arr[i];   // invert array
    }

    int invertedKadane = kadane(arr);

    int circularMax = totalSum + invertedKadane;

    return max(normalMax, circularMax);
}





